nucleus.presenter

Class Presenter<ViewType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nucleus.presenter.Presenter<ViewType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ViewType - a type of view to return with getView().
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RxPresenter

    public class Presenter<ViewType>
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a base class for all presenters. Subclasses can override onCreate(android.os.Bundle), onDestroy(), onSave(android.os.Bundle), onTakeView(ViewType), onDropView().

    Presenter.OnDestroyListener can also be used by external classes to be notified about the need of freeing resources.

    • Method Detail

      • onCreate

        protected void onCreate(android.os.Bundle savedState)
        This method is intended for overriding. It is being called by PresenterManager.provide(java.lang.Class<T>, android.os.Bundle) method after construction complete.
        Parameters:
        savedState - If the presenter is being re-instantiated after a process restart then this Bundle contains the data it supplied in onSave(android.os.Bundle).

      • onDestroy

        protected void onDestroy()
        This method is intended for overriding. It is being called by destroy() after Presenter.OnDestroyListener listeners are notified about presenter destruction.

      • onSave

        protected void onSave(android.os.Bundle state)
        This method is intended for overriding. It is being called by PresenterManager.save(nucleus.presenter.Presenter) to save presenter's instance state. Later the state can be passed to onCreate(android.os.Bundle) for a new presenter instance after a process restart.
        Parameters:
        state - a non-null bundle which should be used to put presenter's state info.

      • onTakeView

        protected void onTakeView(ViewType view)
        This method is intended for overriding. It is being called by parent presenter class, when a view calls takeView(ViewType)
        Parameters:
        view - a view that should be taken

      • onDropView

        protected void onDropView()
        This method is intended for overriding. Use it to be notified about a view is going to be destroyed.

      • takeView

        public void takeView(ViewType view)
        Attaches a view to a presenter. Call it from the view, after it has been initialized and its state has been restored. Good places for calling takeView(ViewType) are: Activity.onResume(), View.onAttachedToWindow(), Fragment.onResume()
        Parameters:
        view - a view to attach.

      • dropView

        public void dropView()
        Detaches a presenter from a view. Call it for a view, at the beginning of the destruction phase. Good places for calling dropView() are: Activity.onPause(), View.onDetachedFromWindow(), Fragment.onPause()
